data.enText: a set of events, actions, numbers, etc. which have a particular order and which lead to a particular result

data.chText: 他描述了抢劫案发生前的一系列有关情况。
data.enText: He described the sequence of events leading up to the robbery.
the order that events, actions, etc. happen in or should happen in

data.chText: 这些任务必须按一定次序去执行。
data.enText: The tasks had to be performed in a particular sequence.
These pages are out of sequence .

data.chText: （电影中表现同一主题或场面的）一组镜头
data.enText: a part of a film/movie that deals with one subject or topic or consists of one scene
to arrange things into a sequence

data.chText: 测定（整套基因或分子成分的）序列
data.enText: to identify the order in which a set of genes or parts of molecules are arranged

data.chText: 人类基因组的序列现已测定。
data.enText: The human genome has now been sequenced.

simple_means.memory_skill: sequ 跟随 + ence 表性质，状态 → 一个跟一个 → 连续

means: (电影中表现同一主题或场面的)一组镜头
测定(整套基因或分子成分的)序列

ex.chText: 一连串不幸事件使他焦头烂额。
ex.enText: A sequence of misfortunes have plagued him.

ex.chText: 本文按历史顺序论述那些事件。
ex.enText: The paper deals with the events in historical sequence.

ex.chText: 他按事情发生的先后次序解释那些情况。
ex.enText: He explained the facts in the sequence of events.

synonyms.bx: 指事物衔接的次序，可以是发生的先后顺序，也可以是逻辑顺序。

ex.chText: 事故引起了一连串事件。
ex.enText: The accident caused a chain of events.

ex.chText: 他们的行为在全国引发了一系列叛乱。
ex.enText: Their acts set off a chain of revolts throughout the country.

ex.chText: 这一连串事件或许会导致又一场战争。
ex.enText: The chain of events might lead to another war.

synonyms.bx: 指像链条一样连接在一起的一连串事物，有时彼此间含因果关系。

ex.enText: They've had a series of good harvests.

ex.chText: 她听了关于科幻小说写作的系列讲座。
ex.enText: She attended a series of lectures about science fiction writing.

ex.chText: 反对歧视的一系列法规已经颁布。
ex.enText: A series of laws against discrimination have been issued.

ex.chText: 这一荒诞的学说是以一系列错误的设想为依据的。
ex.enText: This ridiculous theory is based on a series of wrong assumptions.

synonyms.bx: 强调是同类事物，可以前后互有关联，也可以各成独立的单位。

ex.chText: 他们取得了一个接一个的胜利。
ex.enText: They won a succession of victories.

ex.chText: 他的话连珠炮似地说了出来。
ex.enText: His words came out in quick succession.

ex.chText: 接连不断的聚会把他们累垮了。
ex.enText: The endless succession of parties wore them out.

synonyms.bx: 强调同类事物或事件的相继出现或发生，侧重于一个接一个的次序，其中并非含有一定的逻辑性。

tr: the action of following in order
example: he played the trumps in sequence

tr: film consisting of a succession of related shots that develop a given subject in a movie
a following of one thing after another in time
example: the doctor saw a sequence of patients

tr: several repetitions of a melodic phrase in different keys
serial arrangement in which things follow in logical order or a recurrent pattern
example: the sequence of names was alphabetical
he invented a technique to determine the sequence of base pairs in DNA

tr: determine the order of constituents in

value.def: A sequence of events or things is a number of events or things that come one after another in a particular order.

example.ex: ...the sequence of events which led to the murder.
example.tran: 导致谋杀发生的一连串事件

example.ex: ...a dazzling sequence of novels by John Updike.
example.tran: 约翰·厄普代克令人惊叹的系列小说

value.def: A particular sequence is a particular order in which things happen or are arranged.

example.ex: ...the colour sequence yellow, orange, purple, blue, green and white...
example.tran: 黄、橙、紫、蓝、绿、白的颜色顺序

example.ex: The chronological sequence gives the book an element of structure.
example.tran: 时间顺序让这本书有了一定的结构。

value.def: A film sequence is a part of a film that shows a single set of actions.

example.ex: The best sequence in the film occurs when Roth stops at a house he used to live in.
example.tran: 电影中最棒的一组镜头出现于罗思在他曾住过的一幢屋子前驻足时。

value.tran: (电影中描述某一组动作的)连续镜头,片段

value.def: A gene sequence or a DNA sequence is the order in which the elements making up a particular gene are combined.

example.ex: The project is nothing less than mapping every gene sequence in the human body.
example.tran: 这个项目就是要绘制人体所有基因序列的图谱。

example.ex: ...the complete DNA sequence of the human genome.
example.tran: 人体基因组的完整 DNA 序列

partsOfSpeech.dec: con 加强 + secut 跟随 + ive …的 → 一个跟一个 → 连贯的
con 加强 + sequ 跟随 + ence 表行为 → 随后发生 → 后果
ob 加强 + sequ 跟随 + ious …的 → 拼命跟随的 → 谄媚的
per 加强 + secut 跟随 + e → 跟在后面〔坏你的事〕→ 迫害
per 加强 + secut 跟随 + ion 表名词 → 迫害
pro 在前 + secut 跟随 + e → 跟随〔法官〕在他面前〔告状〕→ 控告
sequ 跟随 + acious 多…的 → 跟风的 → 盲从的
sequ 跟随 + ence 表性质，状态 → 一个跟一个 → 连续
sequ 跟随 + ent 具有…性质的，关于…的 + ial …的 → 连续的
sub 接近 + sequ 跟随 + ence 性质，状态，行为 → 紧跟在后面 → 随后发生的事
